steps.data:
RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -yq --no-install-recommends \
    build-essential \
    git \
    git-lfs \
    curl \
    ninja-build \
    ffmpeg \
    poppler-utils \
    aria2 \
    python3-dev \
    python3-pip \
    software-properties-common \
    && apt-get clean \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

RUN pip3 install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel

ENV CUDA_HOME=/usr/local/cuda
ENV PATH=${CUDA_HOME}/bin:${PATH}
ENV LD_LIBRARY_PATH=${CUDA_HOME}/lib64:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}
ENV CUDA_LAUNCH_BLOCKING=1
ENV TORCH_USE_CUDA_DSA=1

RUN if [ -d "/usr/local/cuda-12.8" ]; then \
      echo "Linking libraries from /usr/local/cuda-12.8" && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda-12.8/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libcudart.so /usr/lib/libcudart.so && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda-12.8/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libcublas.so /usr/lib/libcublas.so && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda-12.8/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libcublasLt.so /usr/lib/libcublasLt.so && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda-12.8/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libcufft.so /usr/lib/libcufft.so && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda-12.8/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libnvrtc.so /usr/lib/libnvrtc.so; \
    elif [ -d "/usr/local/cuda" ]; then \
      echo "Linking libraries from /usr/local/cuda" && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libcudart.so /usr/lib/libcudart.so && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libcublas.so /usr/lib/libcublas.so && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libcublasLt.so /usr/lib/libcublasLt.so && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libcufft.so /usr/lib/libcufft.so && \
      ln -sf /usr/local/cuda/targets/x86_64-linux/lib/libnvrtc.so /usr/lib/libnvrtc.so; \
    else \
      echo "Warning: Could not find CUDA directory for symlinking." ; \
    fi
RUN pip install --pre -U xformers torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/nightly/cu128

#install
RUN pip install triton
RUN pip install sageattention
#RUN MAX_JOBS=4 pip install flash-attn --no-build-isolation

ENV BNB_CUDA_VERSION=128
ENV USE_COMPILE_API=1
ENV CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0
RUN python3 -c "import torch; print('PyTorch version:', torch.__version__); print('CUDA available:', torch.cuda.is_available()); print('CUDA version:', torch.version.cuda)"
RUN python3 -c "import bitsandbytes as bnb; print('BitsAndBytes version:', bnb.__version__)" || echo "BitsAndBytes import check complete"
